-route_trunk_with_cluster_target_size     # global control of trunk routing
                                          # pattern for nets with TRUNK pattern
                                          # attribute. 0: nets with TRUNK
                                          # pattern will be routed as Steiner
                                          # tree; 1: default, nets will be
                                          # routed as traditional trunk
                                          # pattern, i.e., each pin directly
                                          # connects to SNET trunk separately;
                                          # >1: define a proximate max cluster
                                          # size (in number of pins), and nets
                                          # will be routed as fishbone style,
                                          # i.e., several pins in a column are
                                          # clustered together, and then
                                          # connects to SNET trunk.
                                          # (int, default=1)
